text: Jørgen Rostrup (born 5 November 1978) is a Norwegian orienteering competitor, two times winner of the World Orienteering Championships, Short distance in 1999, and Classic distance in 2001.World Orienteering Championship, senior statistics 1966-2006 (Retrieved on December 3, 2007) He also obtained bronze on the Short distance in 2001. He is two times Relay World Champion, as member of the Norwegian winning teams in 2004 in Sweden, and 2005 in Japan. He won gold medal twice in the Junior World Championships, in 1997 and 1998. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1978 births Category:Living people Category:Norwegian orienteers Category:Male orienteers Category:Foot orienteers Category:World Orienteering Championships medalists
